00:51:49,599 --> 00:51:53,321
certain other factions in the game might find that highly unfair and favoritist,

804
00:51:53,822 --> 00:51:57,024
and we know EVE players aren't the most forgiving in that sense.

805
00:51:57,084 --> 00:51:57,945
So how do you deal with that?

806
00:51:59,422 --> 00:52:05,966
Thing is, dealing with material made by players that are connected to factions and stuff like that,

807
00:52:07,547 --> 00:52:10,389
we don't have to deal with a lot of follow-up from it.

808
00:52:10,449 --> 00:52:12,211
I hope it's because we pick them well.

809
00:52:13,371 --> 00:52:17,334
And like I said, I'm aware that I'm, for example,

810
00:52:17,374 --> 00:52:20,536
I'm commissioning a video from a guy who's in Pandemic Legion,

811
00:52:20,576 --> 00:52:24,279
who's one of the constantly warring factions of EVE Online,

812
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:33,085
I mean, I'm aware that their enemies might not like it, but we tend to pick people who have a reputation of already doing good things.

813
00:52:33,786 --> 00:52:37,669
They make material that appeals to a wide group of people.

814
00:52:38,049 --> 00:52:43,974
We don't allow for any direct propaganda for anyone, so we want people to keep that separate.

815
00:52:45,464 --> 00:52:48,790
So we don't host propaganda, unless we advertise for

